    - "itertools.chain.__doc__.__len__() == 190 — the chain docstring is 190 characters long on Python 3.14.3. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.chain.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — chain is a C extension type in itertoolsmodule.c; its MRO is (chain, object). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.islice.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — islice is a C extension type in itertoolsmodule.c; its MRO is (islice, object). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.groupby.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — groupby is a C extension type in itertoolsmodule.c; its MRO is (groupby, object). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.product.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — product is a C extension type in itertoolsmodule.c; its MRO is (product, object). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.chain.__module__ == 'itertools' — chain is defined in the itertools C extension module. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "itertools.islice.__module__ == 'itertools' — islice is defined in the itertools C extension module. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

